# strings

ASCII codes :
A  65      a  97       0 48
B  66      b  98       1 49
C  67      c  99       2 50
.          .           .
.          .           .
.          .           .
Z  90      z  122      9 57

Total ascii codes : 0 to 127 hence total 129 ascii codes 
One ascii code can be represented by 7 bits 

2 ^ 7 = 128

Character is stored in 1 byte in RAM 

Unicodes : represent natural languages
represented in 2 bytes i.e. 16 bits
Unicodes are stored in HEX 
4 HEX digits 
